President Muhammadu Buhari has asked Nigerians to vote for Bola Tinubu, presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the February 25 presidential election. Buhari in a tweet via his verified Twitter account on Sunday, described the former Lagos governor as a reliable person, a true believer in Nigeria who will build on his achievements. “I am not a contestant in the coming election, but my party, @OfficialAPCNg, has a candidate in the person of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu,” Buhari said. ” I am calling on all of you to vote for @officialABAT. He is reliable, a true believer in Nigeria, and he will build on our achievements.” I am not a contestant in the coming election, but my party, @OfficialAPCNg, has a candidate in the person of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu. I am calling on all of you to vote for @officialABAT. He is reliable, a true believer in Nigeria, and he will build on our achievements. pic.twitter.com/RMHlCFuOiy — Muhammadu Buhari (@MBuhari) February 19, 2023 